1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,240
 Yeah, I bring greetings from everybody in Wan Chai.

2
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:04,440
 They are so excited about what's happening here.

3
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:07,500
 And we often talk about you over there in Wan Chai

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:11,080
 and just grateful for the way in which the church has grown.

5
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:14,680
 Today was actually a monumental moment in my ministry,

6
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:16,840
 sort of, I guess, history.

7
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:19,880
 I preached my very first sermon in Cantonese

8
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:23,320
 at the 9.30 service.

9
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:25,200
 The sermon was about a minute long

10
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:30,320
 because I exhausted all of my Cantonese in about 60 seconds.

11
00:00:30,320 --> 00:00:31,280
 But I think it went pretty well.

12
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:32,120
 How did it go?

13
00:00:32,120 --> 00:00:32,960
 What did you think?

14
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:33,780
 It was awesome.

15
00:00:33,780 --> 00:00:35,040
 Awesome, there you go, all right.

16
00:00:35,040 --> 00:00:36,420
 (laughing)

17
00:00:36,420 --> 00:00:38,600
 Now, I have a little bit more English than I do Cantonese,

18
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,240
 so this sermon will not be a minute long.

19
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:42,520
 I apologize for that.

20
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:44,680
 But when Tim reached out and said,

21
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:47,200
 "Hey, I'd love you to come and speak.

22
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:49,260
 "We're doing a series on following Jesus,

23
00:00:49,260 --> 00:00:51,120
 "what it means to follow Jesus."

24
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:52,680
 I was so excited.

25
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:56,640
 I gave my life to Jesus when I was 20 years old.

26
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:59,440
 So I've followed Jesus now, or tried to follow Jesus,

27
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:02,720
 been learning to follow Jesus for about 30 years now.

28
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,480
 And if you're anything like me,

29
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:06,360
 you've come to realize that following Jesus

30
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:08,400
 is a lifelong pursuit.

31
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:11,120
 It's not a easy thing all the time,

32
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:13,600
 but it leads you into the greatest experience

33
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:15,760
 of life that there is.

34
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,180
 But one of the things that I've recognized

35
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:20,240
 as I've been trying to follow Jesus

36
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:23,560
 is just the understanding that in doing that,

37
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:25,640
 I'm often called to live in a way

38
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:27,860
 that I was not expected to live.

39
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:32,680
 I love this moment in Matthew 16, verse 24,

40
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:34,560
 where Jesus says to his disciples,

41
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:36,060
 he says, "If you wanna follow after me,

42
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:37,160
 "here's what you need to do."

43
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:39,240
 He says, "You need to deny yourself,

44
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:42,240
 "pick up your cross, and then follow me."

45
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,600
 So if we have this question of

46
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:46,600
 what does it mean to follow Jesus,

47
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,180
 Jesus says to his disciples,

48
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:50,360
 teaches to his disciples the direct thing.

49
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:54,120
 He says, "Deny yourself, pick up your cross,

50
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,440
 "then you're following me."

51
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,360
 Now, I don't know about you,

52
00:01:57,360 --> 00:02:00,220
 but I don't think this is what the disciples

53
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,240
 were hoping to hear when Jesus says,

54
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:04,820
 "Here's how you can live the best life," right?

55
00:02:04,820 --> 00:02:06,920
 They weren't wanting to hear,

56
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,560
 "Deny yourself, pick up your cross,"

57
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:12,800
 which essentially was like, "Go to a place of death."

58
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,880
 That's not the kind of sort of life

59
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,960
 that they were hoping to sign up for.

60
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:20,040
 I think the disciples were hoping

61
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,780
 that Jesus was gonna say something like this,

62
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:24,060
 "Anybody who wants to come after me

63
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:26,480
 "is going to receive all of my blessings,

64
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,440
 "is gonna live an amazingly relaxed and easy life,

65
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:33,160
 "and I'm gonna follow them the rest of their lives."

66
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,600
 Like, I think for many of us,

67
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,660
 that's what we would love in our faith.

68
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:39,460
 That's kind of what we would love in our religion.

69
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,000
 If that was the reality,

70
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,640
 I think a lot of people would be

71
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,160
 wanting me to be a part of that.

72
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,360
 Like, could you imagine a God who is like,

73
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,600
 "You're gonna have every blessing for me every single day,

74
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,120
 "you're gonna have a perfect and easy life,

75
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,220
 "everything's gonna go well,

76
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:53,900
 "and I'm gonna dedicate myself to following you.

77
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:55,720
 "Like, I'm gonna be there with you every step of the way,

78
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:57,840
 "I'm gonna follow you and make everything awesome for you."

79
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:58,880
 I mean, if you told people that,

80
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:01,400
 they'd be like, "Where do I sign up for that?"

81
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:04,680
 But that's not what Jesus said.

82
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:07,080
 Jesus actually said the opposite.

83
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:08,980
 He said, "If you wanna know what following me is like,

84
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:09,860
 "here's what it's like.

85
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:14,280
 "You need to deny yourself, pick up your cross,

86
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:16,280
 "and then follow me."

87
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:18,600
 Jesus flips the script,

88
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:21,240
 which is kind of what Jesus does all the time.

89
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:24,020
 He actually introduces us to this beautiful,

90
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:26,700
 but challenging, counter-cultural nature

91
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:27,760
 of the kingdom of God.

92
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:30,580
 Counter-cultural, counter-intuitive at times,

93
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:34,000
 counter our expectations often.

94
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,080
 Now, the kind of life that we're called into

95
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:40,160
 is to discover the world as it was truly meant to be.

96
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,700
 And I think when Jesus says this to the disciples,

97
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,720
 "This is how I want you to live your life,"

98
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:47,000
 Jesus understands that the way in which

99
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,080
 we live our lives currently is not the way

100
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:51,480
 that we have been created to live.

101
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,880
 Jesus understood the reality of what sin had done

102
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:56,760
 in humanity, the reality of what sin was doing

103
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:58,320
 in the lives of people,

104
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:01,560
 and the ways in which we treated one another.

105
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,360
 And when people were like, "What do we do to follow you?"

106
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,020
 He's saying, "Okay, here's what it is.

107
00:04:05,020 --> 00:04:09,800
 "We are so kind of overwhelmed by sin and by brokenness

108
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,540
 "that the way we're treating one another

109
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:13,000
 "and the way that we're living right now

110
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,180
 "does not reflect what I created you for,

111
00:04:16,180 --> 00:04:18,040
 "nor what the world has been created for.

112
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:20,440
 "So in order for you to change yourself,

113
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:23,020
 "you're gonna have to literally go through a process

114
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:25,720
 "of your own death and resurrection."

115
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:28,000
 I mean, that's what he's saying.

116
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,960
 He's saying, "You wanna know what life is truly like?

117
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,500
 "In order to experience it, you're gonna have to go

118
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:34,560
 "through a death and resurrection.

119
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:37,320
 "You're gonna have to deny yourself, pick up your cross,

120
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:39,720
 "and then you will get to experience it."

121
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:42,200
 Jesus, I think, teaching this,

122
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:46,760
 as we die to the world around us

123
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:49,880
 and actually begin to live as Christ has called us to do,

124
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,960
 we actually then get to see the world

125
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:54,280
 as it was truly created to be.

126
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:58,760
 Like we begin to see the world differently.

127
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,600
 We begin to understand the world differently.

128
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:02,120
 We begin to have different desires

129
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,480
 than the ones that we used to have.

130
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,960
 We begin to see the world through the eyes and the lens

131
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:08,800
 and the heart and the character of Jesus.

132
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:11,080
 And we begin to see the world come alive

133
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,600
 like it had never come before.

134
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,600
 And Jesus is like, "I want you to experience

135
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,240
 "the world like that.

136
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,480
 "I want you to see the world how I see it.

137
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,340
 "I want you to live in the very way

138
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:21,580
 "that you've been created to be.

139
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:23,800
 "But just in the same way for me,

140
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,860
 "there was a death and resurrection

141
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:28,960
 "to shift the whole world into this new way of being.

142
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,000
 "So if you wanna follow me,

143
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,680
 "are you willing to go through your own death

144
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,920
 "and resurrection?"

145
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,960
 Death to the sin and the brokenness

146
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,760
 and resurrection into new life,

147
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:45,240
 thrilled with my spirit and my hope.

148
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:47,200
 Deny yourself, pick up your cross,

149
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,820
 and then you will follow me.

150
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:49,840
 This is the reality.

151
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:53,460
 A call to following Jesus

152
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:56,680
 is a call to living a radically new way of life

153
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:58,440
 that is the opposite

154
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:01,880
 to how the world currently presents itself to us.

155
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:04,280
 And when we do that and we do that well,

156
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,040
 it's like we give the world a glimpse

157
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,340
 of what heaven on earth looks like.

158
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:10,440
 Are you following this?

159
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:12,000
 This is what Jesus's heart is.

160
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,960
 He's like, "If you were to live that way,

161
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:17,300
 "this radically new way in the world right now,

162
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,520
 "you would begin to show the world

163
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:20,020
 "that there is a different way to live,

164
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:21,620
 "that there is another narrative

165
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:23,640
 "than the narrative of sin and death,

166
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:25,660
 "that there's another way of understanding this world,

167
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:27,400
 "and there's a way of seeing the world

168
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,420
 "in the way that it was really created to be,

169
00:06:29,420 --> 00:06:31,320
 "a bit of heaven on earth."

170
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:34,040
 That prayer that he taught the disciples to pray.

171
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,600
 Pray this.

172
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,680
 Our Father who art in heaven, hallowed be your name.

173
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:42,720
 Your kingdom come, your will be done

174
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,600
 on earth as it is in heaven.

175
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,460
 And when Jesus speaks to the disciples and says,

176
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:49,800
 "You wanna know what it's like to follow me?"

177
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:53,320
 It is like living in such a radically different way

178
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,920
 than you naturally want to live,

179
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:59,020
 that literally people see a bit of heaven on earth.

180
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:04,120
 That, my friends, is what the Beatitudes

181
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,840
 and the Sermon on the Mount are all about.

182
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:09,160
 When Jesus starts teaching the crowds

183
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,380
 and the disciples around him

184
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:11,960
 in that famous Sermon on the Mount,

185
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,200
 he starts by showing them a vision

186
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,680
 of what living could look like in his kingdom.

187
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:21,480
 And each of the Beatitudes are a statement from God

188
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:26,480
 of saying, "Those that live like this will experience this."

189
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,060
 And Chapman did a great job last week

190
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:31,560
 showing us what the first four of those Beatitudes are.

191
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,380
 And he spoke last week about how they help us

192
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:35,800
 to understand that vertical relationship

193
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,720
 that we have with God.

194
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,640
 And what we're gonna do today

195
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:41,120
 is we're gonna look at the next three that are there.

196
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,840
 And these three actually help us to begin to understand

197
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:46,760
 our horizontal relationship with one another.

198
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:49,480
 And before I open the passage, I wanna say this to you.

199
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,480
 What I'm gonna say today

200
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,240
 is gonna be incredibly challenging.

201
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:56,080
 Because Jesus does not hold back the punches

202
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,960
 in these three Beatitudes.

203
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,660
 He's dealt in the first four

204
00:07:59,660 --> 00:08:02,360
 with how we can find that reconciliation,

205
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,040
 that new creation with him.

206
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:04,880
 But then he says,

207
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:08,600
 "The way you're treating one another is not right.

208
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:14,560
 "And those in my kingdom get to experience it like this."

209
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,600
 And when I read these three parables

210
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,720
 about this horizontal relationship with one another,

211
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,320
 I feel deeply challenged.

212
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:25,000
 'Cause I recognize that I don't naturally live like that.

213
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:29,960
 And I find that is a wonderful encouragement

214
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:32,040
 and an invitation to begin to think,

215
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:35,200
 do I want to live differently

216
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:38,320
 so that the world might see something different of God?

217
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,660
 Let me read these three parables to you.

218
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:43,360
 It's found in Matthew 5,

219
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,280
 and we're gonna start in verse seven.

220
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,720
 Listen to this.

221
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:51,720
 Blessed are the merciful, for they will be shown mercy.

222
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:57,080
 Blessed are the pure in heart, for they will see God.

223
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:59,960
 Blessed are the peacemakers,

224
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,040
 for they will be called children of God.

225
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:04,200
 Just stop for a moment

226
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,160
 and take a look at these three side by side.

227
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:09,760
 Blessed are the merciful, for they will be shown mercy.

228
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,920
 I don't know when the last time was

229
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:13,840
 that I felt naturally to be merciful.

230
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:17,580
 In fact, I find a lot easy to hold onto grudges

231
00:09:17,580 --> 00:09:20,480
 and hold onto unforgiveness and find bitterness within me.

232
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:23,040
 Blessed are the pure in heart.

233
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,280
 I don't know when the last time was

234
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:27,800
 that I naturally felt pure in heart towards people.

235
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,760
 In fact, I harbor mixed motives often.

236
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:35,200
 And I look at people and I judge them for who they are

237
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,360
 or maybe for the way they look or the way they act.

238
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:40,600
 And I find all those things wrestling inside of me.

239
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,000
 Blessed are the peacemakers.

240
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,640
 I don't know when the last time was

241
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:47,240
 that I felt naturally wanting to just put everybody

242
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,760
 into a beautiful place of peace.

243
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,880
 Actually, I quite like holding onto the fact

244
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:52,820
 that I'm right and they're wrong.

245
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:56,020
 And I find I read these three things

246
00:09:56,020 --> 00:09:58,360
 and I find that there's a challenge within them

247
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,520
 so beautifully.

248
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,280
 And it's almost like Jesus is trying to bring

249
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,680
 that challenge 'cause he's like saying,

250
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:07,560
 "I'm so tired of how people hold onto unforgiveness.

251
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:10,220
 "I'm so tired that people expect to be treated

252
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:12,080
 "how they treat people.

253
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:14,960
 "I'm so tired by this reality that we do judge

254
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:17,300
 "and we are cynical towards one another

255
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:18,880
 "and we look at one another

256
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:21,160
 "and we cast each other into doubt

257
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:23,440
 "or we have this sort of judgment in our heart.

258
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,560
 "I am sad.

259
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,920
 "I find it frustrating that so many people

260
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:29,280
 "would rather be divided than united,

261
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:32,180
 "hold onto their truth at the expense of somebody else.

262
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:35,400
 "Like this is not the way that I created you to be.

263
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,320
 "I created you to be different from this.

264
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,960
 "I created you to live in such a way

265
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,420
 "that in living so differently

266
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:43,840
 "to how everybody else is living around you,

267
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,900
 "people will lean into that and say,

268
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:47,740
 "I wanna be a bit like that.

269
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:50,240
 "I wanna see that.

270
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:54,400
 "I want to also be like that."

271
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,960
 So Jesus brings these three challenging parables

272
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,640
 next to each other and he says,

273
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:01,960
 "This is what it is."

274
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:04,720
 These beatitudes of this great picture

275
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:07,000
 of the kingdom of God and he says,

276
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,240
 "Will you live like this?"

277
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:12,240
 And we could spend a lot of time on them

278
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,780
 but I wanna jump to,

279
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:16,140
 as I was praying for us here this morning actually,

280
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:17,440
 I was asking the Lord and saying,

281
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,480
 "Which of these is the most important?

282
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,340
 "Which are the ones that we should really lean into,

283
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:23,040
 "unpack in detail?"

284
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:25,280
 I felt the Holy Spirit lead me to the final one,

285
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:27,880
 "The blessed are the peacemakers

286
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:29,920
 "for they will be known as children of God."

287
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:33,000
 And I thought to myself, this is so important

288
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,800
 because I think if there's anything

289
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:36,960
 in terms of how we're treating one another

290
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:39,240
 that the world is broken in right now,

291
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,020
 it's this idea of division.

292
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,120
 I don't know if you've noticed this

293
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:45,340
 but the world is more divided than it has ever been.

294
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:47,600
 That there seems to be this rising rhetoric

295
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:50,440
 around our world about division

296
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,820
 and about turning on others,

297
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:55,200
 about bringing people away from one another

298
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,280
 rather than trying to bring people together.

299
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,160
 And this is happening,

300
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:01,520
 this division at every level of society.

301
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:04,160
 I mean, think about it on a geopolitical level.

302
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,080
 I don't know if you followed all the news in Davos

303
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:08,600
 this past week but there's a group of people

304
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:11,120
 that are trying to create a brand new world order

305
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:14,520
 that will benefit them at the expense of others.

306
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:16,200
 I don't know if you've seen some of the rhetoric

307
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,400
 that is coming out of some of our global leaders

308
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:20,520
 at the moment, rhetoric which basically says,

309
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:22,960
 this is for us and not for the other.

310
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:26,560
 World nations are pushing against each other

311
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,960
 more and more than ever before.

312
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:32,800
 Caesar-like leaders are creating empires

313
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:35,680
 and determining who should be in and who should be out.

314
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:38,200
 And you see this happening on a global level

315
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:41,360
 and you begin to wonder what is going on.

316
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,640
 But then you take it to the city-wide level

317
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:44,720
 and you take a look at what's happening

318
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,160
 even here in Hong Kong.

319
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:48,080
 I don't know if you realize this

320
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,680
 but latest statistics would show

321
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,080
 that the wealthier are getting wealthier in our city

322
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,400
 and the poorer are getting poorer.

323
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:57,240
 There's a growing division between the classes in our city.

324
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:59,640
 There's a growing division in Hong Kong

325
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:02,160
 between the ethnic groups in our city as well.

326
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:04,040
 In fact, some of the latest reports that have come out

327
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,180
 have suggested that there is a racism

328
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:08,440
 towards certain ethnic groups in our city

329
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:12,020
 that has raised itself more in the last five years.

330
00:13:12,020 --> 00:13:15,760
 And then if you take a look at some of the political things

331
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,900
 that are happening, not just here in Hong Kong

332
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:19,880
 but around our region,

333
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:22,040
 families are still being divided in our city

334
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,440
 around political lines, around thoughts of that.

335
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:27,920
 We're seeing more division in Hong Kong than ever before.

336
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:31,120
 That's not the Hong Kong that I think Jesus died for.

337
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:34,720
 And then what about the family level?

338
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,520
 Again, don't know if you're aware

339
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,480
 but there are more divorces in our city

340
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:41,280
 recorded than ever before.

341
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,920
 There's a brokenness at the family level

342
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:45,640
 that we need to be aware of, a division that has come.

343
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,240
 There are more people where the parents

344
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,380
 are not talking to the children

345
00:13:48,380 --> 00:13:50,420
 and the children are not talking to the parents.

346
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:52,420
 I work for a charity, I'm on the board of a charity

347
00:13:52,420 --> 00:13:54,780
 that works with children here in Hong Kong.

348
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:56,460
 And again, I don't know if you recognize this

349
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,740
 but there is more child abuse in our city

350
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:00,460
 and there's more child abuse being recorded

351
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:01,780
 in our city than ever before.

352
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:04,900
 There's more child abandonment in our city

353
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:05,900
 than ever before.

354
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:09,180
 This is the family unit getting broken and divided.

355
00:14:09,180 --> 00:14:12,260
 But then take it down to that personal level,

356
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:15,220
 the level that you and I are at each individually.

357
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:17,540
 And you take a look at our social media feeds

358
00:14:17,540 --> 00:14:21,200
 and the reality of the algorithms that derive those feeds

359
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:24,980
 which don't drive them to unite but drive them to separate.

360
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:27,740
 The echo chambers that are created by what we like

361
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:29,380
 and listen to and watch and whatever.

362
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:32,440
 And then our feeds getting flooded with things like that

363
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:35,460
 which often divides us from those around us

364
00:14:35,460 --> 00:14:36,660
 that might have different perspectives,

365
00:14:36,660 --> 00:14:39,340
 different opinions or even live in a different culture

366
00:14:39,340 --> 00:14:40,380
 or in a different way.

367
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:43,140
 Even on the individual level,

368
00:14:43,140 --> 00:14:44,860
 we're becoming more and more divided.

369
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:46,380
 So whether it's geopolitically,

370
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:47,580
 whether it's within our city,

371
00:14:47,580 --> 00:14:49,880
 whether it's our families, whether it's in ourselves,

372
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,900
 we're in this divided time and you see that

373
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:53,860
 and we should be asking as Christians,

374
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:56,520
 surely there's a better way to live.

375
00:14:56,520 --> 00:15:02,640
 And Jesus says, yes, there is, but it's a hard path.

376
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:05,500
 It's a narrow path.

377
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:09,620
 It's a challenging one, but do you wanna know what it is?

378
00:15:09,620 --> 00:15:11,540
 Let me read it to you one more time.

379
00:15:11,540 --> 00:15:14,020
 It says Matthew 5 verse nine.

380
00:15:14,020 --> 00:15:16,540
 Blessed are the peacemakers,

381
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:19,640
 for they will be called children of God.

382
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:23,060
 It's interesting what Jesus does here.

383
00:15:23,060 --> 00:15:25,580
 In all of the Beatitudes up until this point,

384
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:28,660
 Jesus has had a formula in presenting the Beatitudes.

385
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:31,280
 So he presents something and then he presents

386
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:34,500
 what that thing will get, what they will receive.

387
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:37,020
 So he says, blessed are the poor in spirit,

388
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:39,100
 for they will receive the kingdom of God.

389
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:41,100
 He says then blessed are those who mourn,

390
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:43,180
 for they will receive comfort.

391
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:44,620
 He says, blessed are the meek,

392
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:46,620
 for they will inherit the earth.

393
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:48,620
 Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness,

394
00:15:48,620 --> 00:15:50,080
 for they will be filled.

395
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:52,500
 Blessed are the merciful, so they will get mercy.

396
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,940
 And he goes through all this list

397
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:55,380
 and it's always blessed are this

398
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:56,980
 and here's what they're gonna receive.

399
00:15:56,980 --> 00:16:00,220
 So when he gets the blessed are the peacemakers,

400
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:02,300
 if you're following the formula,

401
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:04,460
 what you expect Jesus to say is this,

402
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:08,500
 blessed are the peacemakers, for they will know peace.

403
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:12,280
 They will receive peace, but that's not what he says.

404
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:15,140
 In fact, he breaks formula at this point

405
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,340
 because I think he has something really important

406
00:16:17,340 --> 00:16:19,460
 to teach his people.

407
00:16:19,460 --> 00:16:22,940
 He says differently, he says, blessed are the peacemakers,

408
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,940
 for they will be called children of God.

409
00:16:25,940 --> 00:16:30,140
 They don't receive something, they get labeled as something.

410
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:33,260
 They get a change, if you will, in status.

411
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:35,300
 People will see the peacemakers

412
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:39,100
 and they will come to see them as people who know me.

413
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:42,280
 Now this is really important that we understand this.

414
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,480
 What Jesus is not teaching here

415
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,760
 is if you become a peacemaker,

416
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:49,160
 then you'll get entry into my family

417
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:51,280
 and I'll call you a child of God.

418
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:53,320
 We know that that's not the way it works.

419
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:56,080
 We know that we enter into being a part of the family of God

420
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,800
 not through our effort, not through what we earn,

421
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,400
 but through the grace that comes

422
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,580
 through the work of Jesus on the cross, amen?

423
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:04,800
 So we're saved into relationship,

424
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:07,440
 into the family of God through that grace.

425
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:11,540
 In fact, let me just read this to you in John chapter one.

426
00:17:11,540 --> 00:17:13,740
 I love how John chapter one captures it.

427
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:17,860
 It says, yet all those who received him, this is Jesus,

428
00:17:17,860 --> 00:17:19,780
 to those who believed in his name,

429
00:17:19,780 --> 00:17:23,460
 he gave the right to become children of God.

430
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:28,420
 So our status as children of God is a right given to us,

431
00:17:28,420 --> 00:17:31,660
 not because we earn it, but because we believe,

432
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:33,140
 because we've repented of our sins,

433
00:17:33,140 --> 00:17:34,580
 we've come into belief of Jesus,

434
00:17:34,580 --> 00:17:35,820
 he's forgiven those sins,

435
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,800
 and we are now a part of his family.

436
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:41,080
 We are saved by grace through faith, amen?

437
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:43,480
 So when Jesus says, blessed are the peacemakers,

438
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,880
 for they will be called children of God,

439
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:47,280
 he's not going against the wider teaching

440
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,800
 of salvation in scripture here.

441
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,560
 He's not saying do this and then you will become this.

442
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:53,320
 Here's what he's saying, it's actually the opposite.

443
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:56,360
 He's saying, as you become people

444
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:58,600
 who make peace in this world,

445
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:01,160
 people will see that and go, wow,

446
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:03,920
 those must be people of God.

447
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,400
 They must be God's people.

448
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,080
 They must be God's children,

449
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,760
 because I know naturally that's not what I wanna do.

450
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:12,000
 I know naturally I wanna harbor bitterness.

451
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:13,900
 I know naturally I wanna be angry.

452
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,960
 I know naturally I'd rather be with my own tribe.

453
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:18,120
 I know naturally that my sin drives me

454
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:20,080
 to divide and not to unite.

455
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:23,480
 So when we see people doing it differently,

456
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:26,700
 people stand back and go, hang on a sec.

457
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:28,920
 How come they're like that,

458
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:32,800
 whereas I feel like I'm like this?

459
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,360
 And I think God stands back,

460
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:36,440
 and when he sees his church,

461
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:39,600
 when he sees people that he knows, believes in him,

462
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:42,360
 begin to live out a peacemaking lifestyle,

463
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:45,120
 he goes, that's my boy.

464
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:46,440
 That's my girl.

465
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,880
 Those are my kids.

466
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,360
 These are my children.

467
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,600
 They are revealing to the world

468
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:54,960
 something that is inherent in my character and my nature,

469
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,540
 and that is to bring reconciliation

470
00:18:57,540 --> 00:18:59,120
 to the things that are divided.

471
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:02,600
 And when we as the church act that way,

472
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:05,760
 when we embrace that character ourselves,

473
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:09,000
 when we begin to live that out before the world,

474
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:12,200
 people see something different,

475
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,440
 and they begin to ask those critical questions.

476
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:17,920
 Why are they like that?

477
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,720
 Blessed are the peacemakers,

478
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:23,160
 for they will be called children of God.

479
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:25,400
 Now, if that's all true,

480
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:28,880
 then here's something I think we have to deeply wrestle with.

481
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:32,040
 Are we proving to be the children of God

482
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:35,200
 in the world's most important hour

483
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:37,360
 where it needs it the most?

484
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:39,480
 'Cause if it's true that there is division

485
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:41,160
 at all elements of society,

486
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,240
 and we're seeing some of that division in our city

487
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,200
 like never before,

488
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,540
 the question I think God has for the church is,

489
00:19:46,540 --> 00:19:49,560
 are we proving ourselves to be the children of God

490
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:52,120
 in a time when the world needs to see those children

491
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:53,240
 more than ever before?

492
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:55,880
 Is the church standing up,

493
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:59,040
 or is the church shrinking back?

494
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,200
 And when we sort of sit with this,

495
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:07,400
 we begin to recognize that what Jesus has to say here

496
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,480
 is not just important on an individual level,

497
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:12,200
 it's important throughout the whole of the structures

498
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,840
 of what society has created.

499
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:17,480
 Could it be that the renewal of all things

500
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:22,000
 sits on those who call themselves the children of God?

501
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,800
 Now, I wanna unpack for you

502
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,300
 what I think Jesus is trying to say

503
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,820
 about how we live as peacemakers

504
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:32,600
 by telling you what Jesus didn't say in this passage, okay?

505
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:34,200
 Here's what Jesus didn't say.

506
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,360
 He didn't say, "Blessed are the peacekeepers,

507
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:40,240
 "for they will be known as the children of God."

508
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:44,760
 Peacekeepers are those who will avoid conflict at all costs,

509
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:46,400
 who will do whatever they can

510
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:49,400
 to move away from the reality of a conflict,

511
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,560
 who will sweep anything under the rug,

512
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:55,280
 do any sort of compromise just to ensure that peace remains.

513
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:58,480
 They avoid conflict, avoid hard conversations,

514
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:01,120
 compromise their values just in order

515
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:03,640
 that there is no one to be upset or distressed.

516
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:05,080
 My wife's sitting here in the front row,

517
00:21:05,080 --> 00:21:07,480
 and she will know that I am a peacekeeper

518
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:09,880
 in my personality and who I am.

519
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,920
 She will tell you that oftentimes,

520
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,480
 if we get into a bit of an argument,

521
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:15,720
 I'm the one who's sweeping stuff under the rug.

522
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:17,200
 I'm the one who's trying to quell everything

523
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,520
 and make everything nice and peaceful.

524
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:20,300
 I will say whatever it takes

525
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:22,200
 to make things peaceful in the house again

526
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,720
 because I hate conflict.

527
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:25,120
 I find it stressful.

528
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,040
 I want to avoid it at all costs.

529
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:28,960
 And here's what peacekeepers do.

530
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:31,000
 They create a false peace.

531
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,680
 Well, we're just not gonna talk about those issues.

532
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,520
 Oh, no, no, no, it's okay.

533
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:36,760
 Let's just pretend like we get along together.

534
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,120
 Let's just kind of ignore the reality

535
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:40,800
 that some really hard conversations,

536
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,920
 that we've really hurt each other.

537
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,120
 Let's not talk about any of that.

538
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:45,080
 Let's just pretend like everything's good.

539
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:46,400
 And if we could pretend like everything's good,

540
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,340
 we'll feel like we've got peace.

541
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:51,580
 This is very dangerous.

542
00:21:51,580 --> 00:21:52,520
 And I think if I'm honest,

543
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:53,640
 I think there's been some times

544
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,700
 in Hong Kong's recent history

545
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:57,800
 where perhaps there's been a false peace created

546
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,800
 and not a true peace.

547
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:02,000
 When we ignore the realities of what's there

548
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:02,920
 that needs to be dealt with,

549
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:05,000
 whether in our families, whether individually,

550
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,100
 or whether in our society as a whole,

551
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:09,920
 we are ending up basically trying to keep peace

552
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:12,800
 at the expense of real peace.

553
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:13,640
 Are you with me?

554
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:18,920
 See, Jesus didn't say, "Blessed are the peacekeepers.

555
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,500
 "They will be children of God."

556
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:23,120
 Jesus offers a different path.

557
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:25,680
 If you look at the way that Jesus operated

558
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:27,700
 in this area of peacemaking,

559
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:30,200
 He was not a peacekeeper.

560
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:33,240
 In fact, Jesus in creating peace,

561
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:36,360
 He wasn't one who embraced sort of self-ignorance

562
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:37,800
 or avoidant behavior.

563
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,800
 Jesus walked right into conflict

564
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,360
 and healed it from the inside out

565
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:46,060
 through sacrifice and hardship.

566
00:22:46,060 --> 00:22:47,320
 I mean, look at every single time

567
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:49,200
 that Jesus brings people together.

568
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,720
 Every single time that Jesus does something

569
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,800
 that brings peace on earth,

570
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,520
 the ultimate obviously being the cross,

571
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,560
 which we'll talk more about in a moment.

572
00:22:57,560 --> 00:22:59,860
 Every single one of them,

573
00:22:59,860 --> 00:23:03,440
 Jesus steps into the midst of a conflict,

574
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:07,200
 braves difficult and hard conversations,

575
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:10,660
 heals it from within through sacrifice and hardship.

576
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:12,520
 That's who He is.

577
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:14,760
 He doesn't say, "Blessed are the peacekeepers,"

578
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:17,880
 but, "Blessed are the peacemakers."

579
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:20,640
 He also didn't say this, "Blessed are the peace lovers,

580
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,400
 "for they will be the children of God."

581
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,480
 Now, that would be great.

582
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:26,680
 Everybody loves the idea of peace.

583
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:28,520
 Everybody loves the values of peace.

584
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:30,480
 Everybody loves to talk about peace.

585
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:33,760
 Everybody loves to tweet or to post on their IG

586
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:36,480
 something that is peaceful or might bring peace.

587
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:39,280
 Everybody loves to have the idea or the concept

588
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,320
 or the thought of peace,

589
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:42,500
 but not that many people are actually willing

590
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,760
 to work for peace,

591
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,780
 who are actually willing to do the hard yards

592
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:48,440
 in the area of peace,

593
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:50,920
 who is able to have that hard conversation,

594
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:52,720
 do some truth speaking,

595
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,200
 call people to repentance,

596
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:56,760
 whatever it might be to do the work,

597
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:58,600
 the deep and important work of peace.

598
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,320
 There are many that won't do that.

599
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:03,760
 And instead, we're just happy to be a peace lover

600
00:24:03,760 --> 00:24:06,160
 or make other people think that we love peace,

601
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:10,680
 but not actually embrace peace the way it truly is.

602
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:13,160
 And Jesus says that actually that's not the way.

603
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,880
 The word He chooses here, interestingly, for peacemaker

604
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,520
 is a unique Greek word.

605
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:19,140
 It's only used in this one instant

606
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:20,520
 in the whole of the New Testament.

607
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:21,800
 It's an action word,

608
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,680
 and it means a lifestyle of action.

609
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:28,520
 So this is not just have a nice idea of what peace is

610
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:30,520
 and proclaim some theory.

611
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:34,720
 This is like dedicate your life to living this out.

612
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:37,300
 So He didn't say blessed are the peace lovers.

613
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:38,920
 Finally, He also didn't say blessed,

614
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:39,760
 and this is a good one,

615
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,800
 blessed are the peace achievers,

616
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:44,360
 for they will be known as the children of God.

617
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:45,640
 I'm really grateful for this one

618
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:46,480
 'cause I don't know about you,

619
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:48,460
 but the times when I've tried to broker peace in my life,

620
00:24:48,460 --> 00:24:49,760
 it's been really hard.

621
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:51,760
 And I don't always get it.

622
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:53,560
 I don't always see peace.

623
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:54,840
 Even though I might desire it,

624
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,600
 I know in some of the relationships in my life,

625
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,960
 I haven't fully seen the peace that I wanted to see.

626
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,080
 And if Jesus has said blessed are the peace achievers,

627
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:02,760
 I think we would all be set up to a standard

628
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:04,800
 that would be very difficult for us.

629
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,640
 The Bible is actually very clear

630
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:09,280
 that the only fullness of shalom, of peace

631
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:10,320
 that will ever come

632
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:13,320
 will come right at the end of all things,

633
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:15,880
 come right when Jesus returns again.

634
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:17,540
 When Jesus comes back, everything,

635
00:25:17,540 --> 00:25:19,560
 no more pain, no more sin, no more brokenness,

636
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,520
 no more hatred, no more division,

637
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:24,800
 everything reconciled around the person of Jesus Christ,

638
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,380
 our shalom, our peace,

639
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:29,520
 really only will be fully achieved when Jesus returns

640
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:33,020
 in this time that we're sitting in this in-between time

641
00:25:33,020 --> 00:25:34,440
 between the work of the cross

642
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:36,760
 and the return of Jesus and the fullness of shalom,

643
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:39,840
 we will not always see peace.

644
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,560
 We will not always see the fullness

645
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:43,560
 of that reconciliation in the here and now.

646
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:46,680
 Does that mean, therefore, that we don't do anything?

647
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,840
 Does it mean that we step away?

648
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:49,320
 No, because Jesus didn't say,

649
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:51,680
 "Blessed are the peace achievers."

650
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:54,340
 He said, "Blessed are the peacemakers."

651
00:25:54,340 --> 00:25:57,400
 Peter would write later beautifully,

652
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,600
 he would say it like this.

653
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:01,640
 He would say, "As long as it determines on you,

654
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,200
 "live at peace with everyone."

655
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:05,400
 In other words, here's your responsibility

656
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:08,120
 to do everything you can to be a peacemaker,

657
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:11,640
 knowing that not every time will somebody reciprocate.

658
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:14,120
 Reconciliation takes two people,

659
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:16,400
 and you might step towards someone,

660
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,600
 but if they refuse to step towards you,

661
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:22,160
 you may not get the fullness of shalom in that relationship.

662
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:25,640
 But Peter says this, "As far as it depends on you,

663
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,880
 "live at peace."

664
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:30,400
 In other words, take your step, do the work yourself,

665
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,240
 be willing to humble yourself,

666
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,600
 call out what it needs to be called out.

667
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,460
 Do that towards them.

668
00:26:37,460 --> 00:26:38,560
 And there'll be those times

669
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:39,960
 where they will do that towards you,

670
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:41,480
 and you will find reconciliation,

671
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,440
 and it will be a wonderful, beautiful thing,

672
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:45,720
 and God will go, "There's my children."

673
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,640
 And then there'll be other times where you step forward,

674
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:49,880
 and the other person does not,

675
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:52,440
 and there's still enmity, and there's still brokenness,

676
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:54,920
 but your heart has done all that it could

677
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:56,440
 to see reconciliation come,

678
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:59,480
 and God will stand back and say, "There's my child."

679
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:01,920
 Blessed are the peacemakers,

680
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:04,000
 for they will be those

681
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:06,480
 who will be called the children of God.

682
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,320
 And when we sit with this,

683
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:10,840
 we realize that Jesus is the ultimate model in all of this.

684
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,120
 If you wanna know what peacemaking really looks like,

685
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:14,840
 you look to Jesus.

686
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:16,360
 And here's the thing about Jesus.

687
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:20,480
 Jesus steps in to heal the greatest division

688
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:23,520
 that has ever been in all of history,

689
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:25,520
 and that is the brokenness and the division

690
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:28,840
 between humanity and God, and God and humanity.

691
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:32,480
 And the one thing that Jesus makes peace on

692
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,400
 centrally in his ministry

693
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:36,440
 is that brokenness between God and humanity,

694
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:37,400
 humanity and God.

695
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,640
 And I wanna show you, Chris,

696
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:40,280
 I'm gonna grab you for a second, darling.

697
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,560
 You're gonna represent humanity,

698
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:45,080
 'cause you're such a beautiful example of humanity.

699
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,240
 You're gonna stand there.

700
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:47,360
 I'm gonna stand over here.

701
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,560
 Now, here's what Jesus did.

702
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:52,920
 Jesus is on the side of God at the start, right?

703
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:54,000
 He's on this extreme.

704
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:57,000
 If this is God over here, and this is humanity over here,

705
00:27:57,000 --> 00:28:00,000
 and there's a division between the two

706
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:03,120
 because of sin, which humanity brought into the picture

707
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:06,280
 and chose to sin, Adam and Eve in Genesis 1 and 2 and 3.

708
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:09,040
 Now, there's this enmity, this brokenness and division

709
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:10,520
 between God and humanity.

710
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:13,000
 Here's what Jesus decides to do.

711
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:17,760
 Incarnate himself to Chris's side, to the human side.

712
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:19,320
 That's the first thing,

713
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:22,200
 which we very rarely do when we're peacemakers.

714
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,720
 It's really hard to understand

715
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,600
 the other person's perspective.

716
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:27,800
 It's really hard to humble yourself,

717
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:30,400
 to understand how somebody else sees something,

718
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:32,480
 what ideas they may have,

719
00:28:32,480 --> 00:28:35,120
 what they're feeling in that division.

720
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:40,120
 Jesus models in the incarnation being on the human side.

721
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:43,280
 Knowing the pain of humanity,

722
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:45,680
 knowing what it feels like to be lonely,

723
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:46,880
 knowing what it feels like

724
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:49,440
 to see that division happening around.

725
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:54,320
 Jesus takes on our suffering in the incarnation,

726
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:59,320
 willing to be in our perspective, but without sin,

727
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:02,560
 showing us that there is another way

728
00:29:02,560 --> 00:29:04,200
 to live as a human being.

729
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:06,320
 Now, I'm gonna get Tim to jump back up here

730
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:08,120
 because I'm gonna be Jesus and you're gonna be God.

731
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:10,560
 You're the father, I'm the son.

732
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:11,560
 You can be the Holy Spirit,

733
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:12,520
 but you're not needed right now.

734
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:13,440
 You can stay there.

735
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,760
 And Chris is gonna remain humanity.

736
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:16,880
 But here's the reality.

737
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:21,880
 Jesus in being human is then able and fully God,

738
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:24,120
 able to now be the bridge between the two.

739
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:28,240
 Now notice this, Jesus on the cross,

740
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:30,600
 nailed with his hands out like this,

741
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:32,960
 takes the hand of the father

742
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:36,120
 through his willingness to take on sin onto his life,

743
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:38,040
 to take on the brokenness of humanity

744
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:39,560
 and take the hand of humanity

745
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:44,080
 and bring the two together for a photo op.

746
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:47,000
 (audience laughing)

747
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,360
 Hold on, no, wait, wait, wait, come on, come on.

748
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:54,360
 Okay, so Jesus brings and reconciles and makes peace,

749
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:58,120
 reconciliation between the father and humanity

750
00:29:58,120 --> 00:29:59,760
 through the forgiveness of sin

751
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:02,760
 by taking that sin onto himself, standing in the gap,

752
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:05,560
 being that bridge so that these two could be back together,

753
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:08,800
 offering that in a freeness and a grace.

754
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,840
 This is the ultimate example of peacemaking.

755
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:13,920
 Are you following that?

756
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:16,160
 Okay, now notice, okay, you can sit down, you can sit down.

757
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:17,840
 Well done, you're done.

758
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:21,040
 But notice this, Jesus does that.

759
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:25,600
 And then he says, "Blessed are those who do the same."

760
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:29,480
 Because when they do that, they show the world

761
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:32,800
 that they have received that reconciliation for themselves.

762
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:35,240
 They begin to show the world that they're my children,

763
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:37,520
 that they are the reconciled ones

764
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:40,120
 who are now, as Paul would say in scripture,

765
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:43,200
 engaged in the ministry of reconciliation.

766
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:47,520
 And so our call is to do what Jesus did.

767
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:49,680
 And of course, our responsibility is not to step in the gap

768
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:51,680
 with sin and take on all of sin onto our shoulders.

769
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:53,720
 That's only Jesus, and Jesus did that

770
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,440
 to free us and reconcile us.

771
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:57,320
 But our now reality is to say,

772
00:30:57,320 --> 00:31:02,320
 how do I incarnate that same process

773
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:05,920
 in the divisions that I see globally,

774
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:10,840
 within my city, in my family, within myself?

775
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:14,080
 How do I step towards the other,

776
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:16,680
 understand from their perspective, hear their pain?

777
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:19,480
 How do I have that empathy, not just sympathy,

778
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:21,360
 but an empathy and a compassion

779
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:22,520
 for what they've gone through?

780
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:25,160
 How do I brave a hard conversation

781
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:27,040
 so that we can bring the two together?

782
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:29,400
 How do I actually stand in the gap, pray,

783
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:32,040
 ask for forgiveness myself, go on that journey,

784
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:33,200
 whatever it might be?

785
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:36,400
 But I am now called as a child of God

786
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:38,800
 to be a reconciler in the world,

787
00:31:38,800 --> 00:31:41,080
 and the world desperately needs it.

788
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,680
 And I think God is standing over the church

789
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,380
 and saying, where are my children?

790
00:31:44,380 --> 00:31:47,320
 Because there's more division than ever before.

791
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:49,340
 Where are my children?

792
00:31:49,340 --> 00:31:51,840
 Where are the ones who have experienced reconciliation

793
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:54,080
 for themselves at the most important level?

794
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:56,360
 And where are they in this world right now?

795
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:58,160
 Because the world desperately needs to see

796
00:31:58,160 --> 00:31:59,600
 something of that reconciliation.

797
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:03,000
 Yes, ultimately, to God as the primary place

798
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:06,320
 of reconciliation, but then towards one another.

799
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:08,360
 Love the Lord your God with all your mind,

800
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:09,520
 heart, soul, and strength,

801
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:11,720
 and love your neighbor as yourself.

802
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:15,560
 We get the great calling and privilege

803
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:18,040
 to be peacemakers.

804
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:25,360
 I became a Christian at the age of 20, I shared earlier,

805
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:28,800
 but I grew up in a Christian home.

806
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:31,840
 My mother and father loved Jesus, loved the church,

807
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:35,200
 and some of my earliest memories of life

808
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,060
 is being in church.

809
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:38,600
 I remember even at the age of four,

810
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:40,840
 seeing my father slain in the spirit.

811
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,440
 My parents were going to a super Pentecostal

812
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:43,520
 charismatic church at the time,

813
00:32:43,520 --> 00:32:46,080
 and I remember seeing my father slain in the spirit,

814
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:47,600
 one of my earliest memories.

815
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:50,520
 I've always seen my parents in church.

816
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:52,760
 That's always been a part of who we are.

817
00:32:52,760 --> 00:32:56,440
 My dad loved the church, loved pastors in particular,

818
00:32:56,440 --> 00:32:58,920
 and really held pastors to a high standard

819
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:00,000
 and a high degree.

820
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:03,160
 My father was a very successful business person,

821
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:05,120
 and that enabled him to be very generous

822
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:07,600
 towards the pastors in the churches that he attended

823
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:09,040
 throughout his life.

824
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:10,480
 And there was one particular church

825
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:13,320
 that my father and my mother were going to for a season,

826
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:15,560
 and he got to know the pastor there really well.

827
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,120
 They got on very closely,

828
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:21,120
 and the pastor had a business idea, a business venture

829
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:22,200
 that he wanted to get into,

830
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,760
 not anything to do with ministry,

831
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:25,040
 but something in the business world,

832
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:26,880
 and knew that my father was somebody

833
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:28,520
 who was accomplished in the business world.

834
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:31,600
 So the pastor asked my father to partner with him

835
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:33,480
 in this business endeavor.

836
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:35,360
 And my father prayed about it, thought about it,

837
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:36,200
 talked to a few people,

838
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,960
 and decided that this would be a great thing to do.

839
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:41,280
 And so he really respected this pastor, really trusted him,

840
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:43,840
 so partnered with him in this business venture.

841
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:46,320
 What it meant was is that my dad worked full-time

842
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:50,280
 for this business that was created by this pastor.

843
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:52,120
 Well, over about a year and a half

844
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:54,080
 of my father being in that business,

845
00:33:54,080 --> 00:33:58,720
 he got to see the real character of this pastor,

846
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:02,640
 and he got to see some really dodgy business practices

847
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:04,360
 which actually culminated

848
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:07,360
 in what my father would say was corruption.

849
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:10,240
 And it broke my father's heart.

850
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:12,800
 All the trust that he had in the church,

851
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:14,560
 all the trust that he had in pastors,

852
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:17,760
 all of the ways in which he had esteemed pastors

853
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,720
 and been so generous to pastors,

854
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:23,040
 and now even given his livelihood over to a pastor

855
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,240
 to do business with him,

856
00:34:24,240 --> 00:34:26,520
 so hurt by the corruption that had happened,

857
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:30,920
 my father was deeply disrupted and pained by this,

858
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:34,760
 so angry at this, so angry, in fact,

859
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:38,640
 that my father decided at that point, he made a vow

860
00:34:38,640 --> 00:34:41,920
 that he would never step foot in a church again,

861
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:45,680
 and that he would never follow or never be around

862
00:34:45,680 --> 00:34:47,680
 or never connect with a pastor again.

863
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:50,040
 He still loved Jesus,

864
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:53,160
 but he made a vow to himself that he was done with pastors

865
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:54,600
 and done with the church.

866
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:59,760
 Now, that's painful just even in and of itself,

867
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:02,280
 but it's even more painful when you consider

868
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:06,880
 that my father made that vow on the very same week

869
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:09,080
 that I became senior pastor here at the Vine.

870
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:13,680
 So I wonder how you might think that would have felt.

871
00:35:13,680 --> 00:35:18,240
 For me, stepping into what was a really big role,

872
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,600
 where I needed a lot of support

873
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:21,240
 and a lot of help and a lot of prayer,

874
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:23,400
 and I'm looking at Nigel, who was around at the time

875
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:25,160
 and knew all about that,

876
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:29,320
 I needed the support of my father, desperately.

877
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:31,360
 Not only that, but I was proud

878
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:33,120
 of becoming senior pastor at the Vine,

879
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:35,440
 and I wanted my dad to be proud of me too.

880
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:37,920
 I wanted my dad to be sitting in the front row,

881
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:40,360
 cheering me on week in and week out.

882
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:43,240
 That's what I desired, and suddenly my father is like,

883
00:35:43,240 --> 00:35:46,080
 I don't want anything to do with pastors anymore

884
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:48,520
 at the same time that I had now become a pastor.

885
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:52,320
 And I remember being so angry at my father,

886
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:58,120
 so angry that he was turning his back on me

887
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:01,400
 at the time when I felt like I needed him the most.

888
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:05,080
 The fact that in about eight years, I think it was,

889
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,520
 between me becoming senior pastor

890
00:36:06,520 --> 00:36:08,080
 and my father passing away,

891
00:36:08,080 --> 00:36:09,840
 in those eight year period,

892
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:12,520
 I think he came to the Vine twice in eight years.

893
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:14,280
 Both of them were on Christmas day.

894
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:20,360
 And I remember feeling deeply inside of myself,

895
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,680
 so much anger,

896
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:27,480
 so much pain that my father had made these choices

897
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:29,440
 and that I felt embarrassed when I was around him,

898
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:31,880
 I felt embarrassed to be a pastor.

899
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:34,000
 So I had to downplay it all the time.

900
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,520
 And I felt like when my dad and I got together,

901
00:36:36,520 --> 00:36:37,760
 we had nothing to talk about anymore

902
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:40,000
 because my whole life was serving God in this way.

903
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,680
 And I knew that he didn't wanna hear about any of it.

904
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:46,440
 And my relationship with my father was deep before

905
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:48,640
 and then became surface.

906
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:52,080
 And then over a couple of years, became very distant.

907
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:55,800
 And we would chat at times about golf or the weather

908
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:58,240
 or about anything that we could try to think of,

909
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:00,000
 but we would never talk about the thing

910
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,360
 that was the most important to me

911
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:03,520
 or the thing that had broken him the most.

912
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:06,280
 And we drifted and drifted and drifted and drifted.

913
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:09,320
 And I remember a number of years into this

914
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:12,120
 feeling so overwhelmed by this division.

915
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,760
 And I remember going to God about it.

916
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:18,280
 And I remember God saying, "Andrew, you need healing first."

917
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:21,880
 And this is often the first start in any peacemaking moment

918
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:24,520
 is to recognize that you have contributed,

919
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:28,480
 that there is some stuff in you that's not quite right.

920
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:31,200
 And I recognized that I was holding anger and bitterness,

921
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:33,480
 frustration towards my father.

922
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:36,440
 I also recognized as I really was honest about it,

923
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:39,400
 that I was feeling that way before God a little bit as well.

924
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:41,520
 Feeling like even God had turned his back on me

925
00:37:41,520 --> 00:37:42,440
 a little bit at the time

926
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:44,600
 when I was moving into this new role.

927
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:47,800
 And I felt like the Holy Spirit was saying,

928
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:49,920
 "Andrew, you need a lot of healing first,

929
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:51,160
 "that I need to deal with something

930
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,240
 "that's going on in your life."

931
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:54,360
 There was some sin I needed to repent of.

932
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:56,400
 There was some brokenness that I needed to deal with.

933
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:58,800
 And I went on a little journey myself of doing that.

934
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:01,560
 And then after I'd felt like I'd gone through some of that,

935
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:03,320
 I was then felt like the Holy Spirit say,

936
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:06,640
 "Okay, you need to be willing to be a peacemaker."

937
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:09,040
 And I remember how hard this was,

938
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:10,680
 but I remember calling my dad and saying,

939
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:12,600
 "Dad, I'd love to get together for lunch with you

940
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,560
 "'cause I wanna have a conversation about something."

941
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:15,920
 My dad had no idea what it was about.

942
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:17,720
 And we met in this Starbucks.

943
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:19,400
 I can picture the Starbucks,

944
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:20,440
 and I can picture every person

945
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:21,640
 that was sitting in that Starbucks.

946
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:23,560
 Have you ever had a moment in life that's so significant

947
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:25,640
 that you just remember everything about it?

948
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:27,000
 And I remember sitting in this Starbucks

949
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:31,800
 and I braved this really hard conversation with my dad.

950
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:35,720
 And I told him how much I had been hurt

951
00:38:35,720 --> 00:38:38,480
 by his decision and choices.

952
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:40,600
 I shared about the anger that I had felt

953
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:42,840
 and the pain that it caused me.

954
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:45,040
 I talked about the abandonment I had felt from him

955
00:38:45,040 --> 00:38:46,320
 and also from God.

956
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:50,560
 And I just began to just pour out all of this stuff to him.

957
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,680
 And he sat there and I had no idea how he was gonna react.

958
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:55,960
 But he sat there and he listened.

959
00:38:55,960 --> 00:38:57,160
 Then he said, "Andrew, I need to tell you

960
00:38:57,160 --> 00:38:58,320
 "my side of the story."

961
00:38:58,320 --> 00:39:00,200
 I'm like, "Yeah, of course."

962
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:02,280
 And he began to talk about how deeply hurt

963
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:03,480
 he had been by this pastor

964
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:05,960
 and how all the trust and faith he had put in him

965
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:08,080
 had been broken.

966
00:39:08,080 --> 00:39:11,920
 And he talked about how it created such anxiety in him

967
00:39:11,920 --> 00:39:13,880
 that any time he stepped in a church

968
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:14,800
 from that point forward,

969
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,360
 just brought him a wave of anxiety

970
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:18,960
 and that anxiety kept him away from church.

971
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,480
 And he said, "I've wanted to be,"

972
00:39:20,480 --> 00:39:22,120
 and I'd never heard him say this,

973
00:39:22,120 --> 00:39:24,160
 but he said, "I wanted to be in that front row

974
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:26,680
 "every week, Andrew, but I just couldn't do it.

975
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:29,840
 "My anxiety and my anger and my bitterness

976
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:30,880
 "kept me from there.

977
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:34,000
 "It wasn't about you, but it was about everything else

978
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,640
 "that was going on, but I just couldn't be there."

979
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:39,000
 And he said, "Sorry," and I said, "Sorry,"

980
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:40,560
 and these two grown men in the Starbucks

981
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:42,280
 started weeping like crazy.

982
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:45,360
 And I'd like to tell you that that instantly

983
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:46,920
 made our relationship super better

984
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,960
 and that suddenly everything was great again

985
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:50,040
 between my father and I,

986
00:39:50,040 --> 00:39:53,080
 but actually there was a journey of a number of years

987
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:54,280
 where we had to actually continue

988
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:56,000
 to have some of those bigger conversations.

989
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:58,760
 But that day was a shift.

990
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:00,160
 It was a breakthrough.

991
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:03,680
 It was a peacemaking moment.

992
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:04,880
 And although there was a journey

993
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:07,520
 towards a deeper relationship between the two of us,

994
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,680
 a journey that enabled us

995
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:10,080
 to have some of those conversations,

996
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:11,800
 and then unfortunately before he died,

997
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:13,680
 we weren't able to have all of them.

998
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:15,560
 But I know that my relationship with him

999
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:18,440
 was so much closer and stronger when he died

1000
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:21,160
 than it was before that day in that Starbucks.

1001
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:22,880
 And I think in that moment in Starbucks,

1002
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:25,320
 God was leaning over us by his Spirit

1003
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:27,120
 and saying, "These are my children.

1004
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:32,760
 "They're doing something that is significant.

1005
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:34,880
 "They are making peace."

1006
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:39,600
 And I wonder what that might mean for you here this morning.

1007
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:43,440
 What does it mean for you to be a reconciler

1008
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,720
 and have this ministry of reconciliation?

1009
00:40:45,720 --> 00:40:46,960
 What does it mean for you to recognize

1010
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:49,840
 that Jesus has done that in the cross for you,

1011
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:52,080
 and as his children, you're called to do that now

1012
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:54,120
 in the world around you?

1013
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:56,880
 What might that look like in your city

1014
00:40:56,880 --> 00:41:00,000
 or in your families?

1015
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:02,100
 What might that look like within yourself?

1016
00:41:02,940 --> 00:41:04,620
 I know that for some of you in this room,

1017
00:41:04,620 --> 00:41:06,660
 you have a similar story to me.

1018
00:41:06,660 --> 00:41:08,420
 Maybe there's a brokenness or a division

1019
00:41:08,420 --> 00:41:09,860
 between you and one of your parents,

1020
00:41:09,860 --> 00:41:12,220
 whether that's your father or your mother,

1021
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:13,580
 and you're wondering whether that rift

1022
00:41:13,580 --> 00:41:17,660
 could ever be broken, sorry, ever redeemed and renewed.

1023
00:41:17,660 --> 00:41:19,140
 For some of you here, perhaps you're feeling

1024
00:41:19,140 --> 00:41:21,700
 a little bit about maybe a sibling

1025
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:23,700
 or an aunt or an uncle within your family.

1026
00:41:23,700 --> 00:41:25,740
 So often, the way the enemy works

1027
00:41:25,740 --> 00:41:27,420
 is to bring division within our families

1028
00:41:27,420 --> 00:41:28,620
 like it happened for me.

1029
00:41:30,020 --> 00:41:32,500
 Perhaps, I wanna say this too,

1030
00:41:32,500 --> 00:41:34,660
 for some of you, it's your marriage.

1031
00:41:34,660 --> 00:41:36,340
 It's between the person that you love the most

1032
00:41:36,340 --> 00:41:39,140
 and that God has given you to be that great support

1033
00:41:39,140 --> 00:41:41,980
 to you in your life, and there's a brokenness there,

1034
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:43,420
 and you're wondering whether there'll ever be

1035
00:41:43,420 --> 00:41:46,500
 any reconciliation in your marriage.

1036
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:47,820
 For some of you, it might be other things,

1037
00:41:47,820 --> 00:41:48,900
 maybe a colleague at work,

1038
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:50,620
 maybe a situation that you're aware of,

1039
00:41:50,620 --> 00:41:53,260
 maybe an injustice that's happened to you or to a friend,

1040
00:41:53,260 --> 00:41:55,700
 and that's created some anger and bitterness and division,

1041
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:58,980
 and God is saying, "Be a peacemaker in that moment."

1042
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:03,100
 Whatever it might mean, understand this,

1043
00:42:03,100 --> 00:42:06,060
 you will never make peace in your own strength.

1044
00:42:06,060 --> 00:42:08,300
 Like me, there was never going to be enough strength

1045
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:10,860
 within me to have that conversation with my father

1046
00:42:10,860 --> 00:42:13,860
 and to bring a conversation that was years in the making,

